Data Scientist/Big Data Engineer		MeetMe		New Hope, PA, US		<div class="rich-text" itemprop="description"><strong>Listing Info<br /><br /></strong>Where did you meet your best friend?<br /><br />At MeetMe, we believe our friends are some of the most important people in our lives. From our highest highs to our lowest lows, our friends support, respect, and encourage us throughout all of life's ups-and-downs, just as we do for them. As the leading social network for meeting new people in the US, and the public market leader for social discovery, our mission is to improve our members’ lives by introducing them to fun and interesting people who share their passions, interests, and ideals. From a vast data set containing over one hundred million members, we employ unparalleled analytical techniques designed to simplify the science of social discovery and identify potential friendships in near real-time. In addition, by fostering positive communication within a safe online environment, we empower our members to start getting to know one another immediately. How do we do this? We call it, Engineering Serendipity.<br /><br />As MeetMe engineers, we believe Engineering Serendipity is more than a kick-ass statement; we believe it’s our goal. From conceptualization through completion, every product and feature we build is designed to improve the friendship-making experience of our members.<br /><br />To this end, Data Scientists provide a wealth of knowledge to our organization and are directly responsible for supporting product development. In their position, Data Scientists are expected to analyze data and to provide high-quality information and guidance to our management team. Given their view of the data, Data Scientists are in the best position to identify business opportunities in regard to improvements in products, features, or engagement.<br /><br />A strong candidate for the role of Data Scientist at MeetMe would be highly interdisciplinary in their qualifications. Experience in data mining, machine learning, statistics, business analytics, and computational linguistics would be invaluable. Likewise, a background in the theory and practice of Mathematics, Computer Science, or Psychology, would position this candidate to participate in the kind of cutting-edge R&amp;D that maintains MeetMe's competitive edge.<br /><br />While individuals with programming experience in Python, R, Java, and the Hadoop ecosystem would be best-equipped to jump right into our environment, flexibility, the ability to learn new programming languages, and the openness to new paradigms in computation are more important than any particular skill.<br /><br /><strong>At a High Level, a Data Scientist At MeetMe Will Be<br /></strong><ul><li>Performing exploratory analysis against billions of records</li><li>Developing and optimizing algorithms to run in real-time/near real-time</li><li>Identifying product features and opportunities</li><li>Working with our Engineering and Product teams to transition research into real-world products</li><li>Developing and implementing algorithms for distributed and parallel analytics</li><li>Remaining current on emerging trends, tools, and technologies in the industry</li><li>Visualizing analysis of structured and unstructured data sets</li><li>Improving the scalability and performance of our existing analytics solutions</li><li>Conducting timely and effective research in response to specific requests (e.g. data collection, summarization, analysis, and synthesis of relevant data and information)<br /><br /></li></ul><strong>Preferred Qualifications<br /></strong><ul><li>Hands-on experience applying appropriate techniques and tools in Machine Learning, NLP, large-scale data transformation &amp; analysis, and Semantic Web concepts to create revolutionary products</li><li>Masters or Doctorate-level education in a related field (e.g. Computer Science, Applied Mathematics, Data Mining, Machine Learning, Statistics, etc.) with a high degree of mathematical/statistical aptitude and proven hands on coding skills</li><li>Experience working with and applying Neural Networks, LDA, SVM, and Clustering algorithms</li><li>Working knowledge of some or all of the following: Java, JavaScript, Python, SQL, PIG, R</li><li>Experience with Hadoop-related tools is highly desirable</li><li>Ability to solve complex problems in a fast-paced environment with limited guidance</li><li>An eye for quality and a willingness to do what is necessary to achieve deadlines in a dynamic environment with frequent priority changes</li><li>Able to work efficiently in teams and/or as an individual</li><li>Top-notch oral and written communication skills<br /><br /></li></ul></div><div class="rich-text" itemprop="description">MeetMe® is the leading social network for meeting new people in the US and the public market leader for social discovery (NASDAQ: MEET). MeetMe makes meeting new people fun through social games and apps, monetized by both advertising and virtual currency. With approximately 75 percent of traffic coming from mobile, MeetMe is fast becoming the social gathering place for the mobile generation. The company operates MeetMe.com and MeetMe apps on iPhone, iPad, and Android in multiple languages including English, Spanish, Portuguese, French, Italian, German, Chinese (Traditional and Simplified), Russian, Japanese, Dutch, Turkish and Korean. For more information, please visit meetmecorp.com.</div>